The paper deals with coding and decoding algorithms for correcting errors in DNA-based data storage, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of redundancy bits to correct errors, which is a topic related to coding theory (cs.CR, cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for linear-time encoding and decoding, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DM).
